projects.name: Tracking the Spread of COVID-19 in India: A Visual Analysis
projects.description: Led a team of 3 in conducting a comprehensive analysis of COVID-19 data in India using Python, Pandas, Matplotlib, and Seaborn, resulting in a 20% increase in data-driven decision-making accuracy through clear visual reports. Designed intuitive visualizations to track the pandemics progress, highlighting key trends and hotspots, which improved public awareness and response strategies by 15%. Assessed vaccination distribution by age and gender, providing insights into the effectiveness of the vaccination campaign, leading to a 10% optimization in vaccine distribution.

projects.name: Public Photography Contest With Live Voting
projects.description: Developed a platform for organizing photography contests with features like live voting, allowing users to cast up to 3 votes per contest, resulting in a 30% increase in user interaction. Created a full-stack web application using React.js, Node.js, and MongoDB, enhancing user experience and platform functionality by 25%. Implemented user registration, photo submissions, and a weighted voting system with JWT-based authentication, ensuring secure and fair contests, improving user trust by 20%.

projects.name: Average Time Quantum Round-Robin Scheduling Algorithm
projects.description: Developed a novel algorithm to enhance traditional round-robin scheduling. Dynamically adjusted time quantum based on remaining execution time and average burst time. Implemented and simulated the algorithm, demonstrating improved efficiency. Achieved a reduction in average waiting time compared to traditional methods.
